# Verification

**Note**: Universal verification principles (checklist structure, runbook requirements, troubleshooting documentation) are covered in master 73-verification-basics.

This rule documents project-specific verification practice and relies on master rules for requirements.

## Pre-Delivery Verification Checklist

Before considering web-scraper changes complete:

- [ ] All tests pass (`pytest -q`)
- [ ] Quality checks pass (`ruff check web_scraper`, `mypy web_scraper`)
- [ ] Site configurations load and validate successfully
- [ ] Playwright scraper executes successfully (test crawl)
- [ ] Corpus snapshots are created with correct layout
- [ ] Manifest files contain required metadata
- [ ] CLI commands work correctly (test all commands)
- [ ] Error handling works (test error paths)

**Note**: This checklist serves as a reminder only. See `.cursor/rules/master/73-verification-basics.mdc` for universal verification checklist structure. See `.cursor/rules/master/70-error-handling-basics.mdc` for error handling verification requirements. See `.cursor/rules/master/71-testing-patterns-basics.mdc` for test coverage verification requirements.

## Playwright Scraper Verification

### Scraper Execution

- Test Playwright scraper with valid site configuration
- Verify scraper returns `list[Page]` with correct structure
- Verify scraper error handling works (test invalid configs)
- Verify scraper retry logic works (test transient failures)

### Scraper Configuration

- Verify Playwright installation (`playwright-doctor`)
- Verify Playwright browsers are installed (`playwright-setup`)
- Verify required environment variables are documented
- Verify optional environment variables have defaults
- Test scraper initialization with dependency injection (for testing)

## Site Configuration Verification

### Configuration Loading

- Verify all site configurations in `sites/` load successfully
- Verify site configurations validate against `SiteConfig` schema
- Verify validation errors provide helpful messages
- Verify missing configurations raise `ConfigurationError`

### Configuration Validation

- Test entrypoints validation (empty list rejected)
- Test max_pages validation (zero/negative rejected)
- Test URL validation (invalid URLs rejected)

## Corpus Output Verification

### Snapshot Layout

- Verify snapshots use correct directory structure: `corpora/{site_id}/{snapshot_id}/`
- Verify snapshot IDs use ISO 8601 format (timestamp-based)
- Verify `pages/` subdirectory exists
- Verify `manifest.json` exists at snapshot root

### Manifest Structure

- Verify manifest contains required fields: `site_id`, `site_name`, `provider`, `snapshot_id`, `created_at`, `entrypoints`, `total_pages`, `formats`, `pages`
- Verify manifest pages array contains required fields: `url`, `title`, `path`, `content_hash`
- Verify manifest JSON is valid and parseable

### Page Files

- Verify page files use safe filenames (no special characters)
- Verify page files are stored in `pages/` subdirectory
- Verify page file paths match manifest entries

## CLI Verification

### Command Execution

- Test all CLI commands: `list-sites`, `show-site`, `crawl`, `chunk`
- Verify commands produce expected output
- Verify commands handle errors gracefully (show friendly messages)
- Verify commands exit with correct codes (0 for success, 1 for errors)

### Error Handling

- Test invalid site configurations (show validation errors)
- Test missing site configurations (show configuration errors)
- Test scraper failures (show scraper errors)
- Verify correlation IDs appear in error messages

## Verification Practices

Web-scraper verification typically includes:

- **Runbook**: Provide copy-paste commands for conda activation, installing dependencies, running quality checks, testing providers, and verifying corpus output
- **Scraper testing**: Verify Playwright scraper executes correctly
- **Configuration testing**: Verify all site configurations load and validate
- **Corpus testing**: Verify snapshot layout and manifest structure
- **CLI testing**: Verify all commands work correctly

**Note**: See `.cursor/rules/master/73-verification-basics.mdc` for universal runbook requirements.

## Troubleshooting

### Scraper Issues

- Verify Playwright installation (`playwright-doctor`)
- Verify Playwright browsers are installed (`playwright-setup`)
- Verify scraper initializes correctly
- Check scraper logs for correlation IDs

### Configuration Issues

- Verify YAML syntax is correct
- Verify all required fields are present
- Check validation error messages for specific field issues

### Corpus Issues

- Verify `corpora/` directory exists and is writable
- Verify snapshot IDs are unique (timestamp-based prevents collisions)
- Check manifest JSON structure matches schema

